rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
A relatively large and permanent human settlement.
Things that are cities:
## Any human settlement in urban and rural areas that is considered as a center of commerce and population (e.g. New York City, Lexington, Blackpool).
## Any equivalent of US cities/towns such as communes, gemeinde, prefectures, etc. (e.g. Velenciennes, Nurburg, Kouroussa Prefecture).
## Historic settlements that no longer exist, including ghost towns, cities of antiquities or even prehistoric settlements (e.g. Hailstone, Bodie, Ephesus).
## Planned towns and planned cities (Welwyn Garden City, Suncadia Washington).
Things that are NOT cities/towns:
## Localized communities within a larger city or town such as neighborhoods (e.g. Capitol Hill, Union Square). Use mso:location.neighborhood for these.
## Postal codes and zip codes (e.g. 90210, 99723) Use mso:location.postal_region for these.
## Census-designated places or CDPs are normally not cities/towns. For example, the town Southbridge is different from Southbridge CDP. Use mso:location.census_district for these.
## Political districts, constituencies and electoral divisions (e.g. California's 10th congressional district, St Austell) Use mso:government.political_district for these.
## Administrative divisions of countries at any level below the country itself and above city or town (e.g. Nebraska, Ontario, Vienne). In these cases use mso:location.administrative_division.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
Anything with spatial extent and a fixed location on Earth. It is something you could find on a map and could be used to provide information about the position of something else.
Things that are locations:
## Cities, towns, municipalities, villages, hamlets, neighborhoods, settlements, communes, etc. (e.g. Long Beach, New York, Debolt, Alberta and Brzozaw Commune).
## Geographic features like lakes, rivers, swamps, oceans, seas, bays, mountains, hills, islands, geologic formations, etc. (e.g. Dead Sea, Dakota Formation and Boracay).
## Man-made structures like buildings, roads, monuments, historic landmarks, racetracks, airports, graveyards, archaeological sites, etc. (e.g. World's tallest thermometer and Valley of the Kings).
## Governmental districts, electorates, and constituencies (e.g. Pennsylvania House of Representatives, District 91, Molonglo electorate, Laderitz Constituency).
## Geographic coordinates (e.g. 36th parallel south and 160th meridian east).
Things that are NOT locations:
## Area codes (e.g. Area code 415).
## Trains (e.g. Overlander).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location
